history.content: Easiest to email Christopher Hunn about enrollment as he can get back to you.

children.subject: You should be able to AI 61B for units if you end up taking neither, not sure about 61B specifically but generally the academic intern position is open to anyone who meets the grade requirement. I believe you officially sign up after the semester starts.
Yes definitely don't worry about being able to AI for 61B. Also don't expect them to get back to you until around the week before classes or so, if my memory is correct.

history.content:
Rising soph here. Was planning to phase 2 Data 8 but since its enrollment ballooned out of control beyond even the wildest expectations, I'm now looking for backup plans... [sigh] go bears

I filled out the interest form/application for 370 when it came out but haven't heard anything back yet. Without 370 or Data 8 I'm below the unit minimum (unless I get to AI for 61B for units, but haven't heard back from that either) so I need to know when to expect a reply for planning purposes. When should I expect results by?

Thanks for reading

-a slightly disgruntled bear
